</style></head><body><h1>SUNPOR Project Roadmap (2-Person Team)</h1>
<p>Simple step-by-step plan based on the official task distribution.<br />
Follow phases in order - later work depends on earlier steps.</p>
<p><strong>Your team split:</strong>
- <strong>Person 1:</strong> DevOps + Backend + Frontend (full application stack)
- <strong>Person 2:</strong> Data Engineer + AI Engineer (data pipeline + machine learning)</p>
<p><strong>Sync rule:</strong> Meet 15 min daily. Person 1 unblocks Person 2 (DB, APIs). Person 2 unblocks Person 1 (signal catalog, data format, ML outputs).</p>
<hr />
<h2>How to use this roadmap</h2>
<ol>
<li>Start with <strong>Phase 0</strong> on your own laptops - build DB, backend, and APIs locally first.</li>
<li>Then move to <strong>Phase 1</strong> - copy the working local setup to the SUNPOR sandbox server.</li>
<li>Work <strong>phase by phase</strong> - both people have tasks in every phase.</li>
<li>Check off tasks when done. Each phase ends with a <strong>joint demo</strong>.</li>
<li>Use existing project files:
   - Architecture: <code>Docs/SUNPOR_ARCHITECTURE.md</code>
   - Signal seed (104 signals, English): <code>Docs/sunpor-inputs/signal_catalog_seed.csv</code>
   - Form seed: <code>Docs/sunpor-inputs/input_form_taxonomy_seed.json</code></li>
</ol>
<hr />
<h2>Phase 0 - Local Development Setup (Before Week 1)</h2>
<p><strong>Goal:</strong> Both developers can run the project on their own machines - local PostgreSQL, backend API, and a shared way to connect. No sandbox server needed yet.</p>
<p><strong>Why first:</strong> Fix schema, APIs, and imports locally. Deploy to sandbox only after it works on localhost.</p>
<h3>Person 1 - DevOps + Backend (local machine)</h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Step</th>
<th>Task</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>0.1</td>
<td>Install tools: Git, Python 3.11+, Node.js 18+, Docker Desktop (optional but recommended)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>0.2</td>
<td>Clone/copy project repo on local machine (<code>PM-Project - Copy</code>)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>0.3</td>
<td>Create Python virtual environment in project root: <code>python -m venv .venv</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>0.4</td>
<td>Install backend deps: <code>pip install -r live_monitor/requirements.txt</code> + add <code>psycopg2-binary</code>, <code>alembic</code>, <code>python-dotenv</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>0.5</td>
<td>Start <strong>local PostgreSQL</strong> (choose one): Docker <code>postgres:16</code> on port <code>5432</code>, OR install PostgreSQL locally</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>0.6</td>
<td>Create local database: <code>sunpor_dev</code> (user/password you control)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>0.7</td>
<td>Add <code>.env.local</code> (do not commit secrets) with <code>DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/sunpor_dev</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>0.8</td>
<td>Point app config away from ZITTA SQLite - use <code>DATABASE_URL</code> from env</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>0.9</td>
<td>Design DB schema (all tables from architecture doc)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>0.10</td>
<td>Create Alembic migrations for core tables</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>0.11</td>
<td>Run migrations locally: <code>alembic upgrade head</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>0.12</td>
<td>Start backend API locally: FastAPI on <code>http://localhost:8001</code> (Swagger at <code>/docs</code>)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>0.13</td>
<td>Verify <code>/health</code> returns OK</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>0.14</td>
<td>Share with Person 2: <code>.env.local.example</code>, migration commands, how to start API</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h3>Person 2 - Data Engineer (local machine)</h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Step</th>
<th>Task</th>
<th>Waits for</th>
