<hr />
<h2>Priority order (from requirements)</h2>
<pre><code>Phase 0     -&gt;  Local dev first (DB + backend on localhost)
Priority 1  -&gt;  Weeks 1-3   (sandbox, signals, APIs, forms)
Priority 2  -&gt;  Weeks 3-4   (data import, production data flowing)
Priority 3  -&gt;  Weeks 5-6   (Process State + Low Production)
Priority 4  -&gt;  Week 7+     (Predictive Quality - structure first)
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h2>Definition of done</h2>
<ol>
<li>System runs on SUNPOR sandbox</li>
<li>Database is fresh and SUNPOR-specific</li>
<li>All SignalExport signals imported and categorized</li>
<li>All input forms implemented</li>
<li>Operators can record events, maintenance, faults, material behavior</li>
<li>Quality data can be entered retrospectively</li>
<li>Material blocks recorded with period + reason</li>
<li>Production runs linked to material type</li>
<li>ML distinguishes production phases</li>
<li>Low Production recognized separately</li>
<li>Predictive Quality structurally prepared</li>
<li>No ZITTA-specific logic in production config</li>
</ol>
